I was in 11th grade when my neighbor's roommate used to play this song. Now, I'm in 12th, but this song is still connected to my memories from 11th grade. Every time I hear it, all those memories come rushing back. I believe many people can relate to the fact that a song can bring back the exact feeling of what you were doing at that time. One day, after I become successful, I will come back, listen to this song, and relive those memories. I hope people will reply to me after some years, reminiscing about these moments.

It was October 20 when he first sent me a request.. I accepted the request ( Ab lgta hai.... why?? ) You know what was different in this, it was my birthday that day too.. starting me hmare bate nhi hoti thi but later thodi thodi hone lge..Then after some time I realized that this boy has become everything for me....hmare roj bate hone lagi.. We just kept looking for excuses to talk all day long!! He always used to listen to me... My all the fhaltu bkwas.. sab sahi jarha tha humne mila bhi tha 2 bari...There was a time when he would start crying when I cried..phir na jane kyu vo mujhse bate km krne laga.. idk why like all the time bolta tha busy hu, presan hu.. Arijit Singh is a playback singer in India who has received the most awards and nominations for the song "Tum Hi Ho" in Aashiqui 2 (2013) Â¹. He has received a total of 9 awards from 10 nominations for this song. Arijit lent his voice for Pritam-composed 2012 film Barfi! and Vishal-Shekhar-composed Shanghai, where the former fetched him Mirchi Music Award for Upcoming Male Vocalist of The Year award and was nominated, in the same category for the latter Â¹.
